                "href": "/profile/Glenn-Sim-5"
            },
            "answer_text": "At the moment I do have few features in mind. Since they are the creators of the Witcher 3 game, i\u2019m assuming we are going to have similar features like: 1)Upgradeable Weapons and Skill Players will probably have the option to kill AIs, do story mission get materials and upgrade weapons or skills. Weapons are likely to be more futuristic theme. 2)Characters Introduction I enjoy reading lores on characters every game I play. Especially The Witcher 3, it was nicely done. So if cyberpunk2077 gonna be a huge scale of a game, I hope they introduce the characters properly. Some developers don\u2019t really pay attention to lores that much. 3)Combat Mechanics Looking forward to see how they are moving forward with the combat mechanics. Probably something similar to Nier Automata where you could call for help from little drones. If we don\u2019t have little drones to help us out, at least have some advance AI navigator to navigate us throughout the free roaming. That\u2019s pretty much some features that I would love to see on cyberpunk2077. Nevertheless, I\u2019m looking forward to the game. ",
