                "href": "/profile/William-Lawson-97"
            },
            "answer_text": "Exploration. Would like to see how much of Night City is actually explorable through interior level design. It\u2019s confirmed to be an integral part of the game, but a relatively specific percentage would be great for gauging. Games taking place in metropolitan settings have tons of backdrop, GTA games for example rely so much on backdrop city design that cities don\u2019t even feel like cities, rather just building cubes.According to the devs, the game wil take a new approach to dialogue and interaction, something they call the \u201cDirective Scene System\u201d, a first-person real time interaction system that no longer locks the player in a cutscene during narrative sequences, gives them more control and adapts to where the player is looking during dialogue, opening up new dialogue and interaction options based on it. Definitely looking to see how that\u2019s going to work out and how much of the interaction will it encompass. On that note, attributes like skill levels and origins are also confirmed to affect dialogue, so looking forward to see where they\u2019re going with that as well.Custom playstyles. The developers frequently mentioned their open-ended gameplay scheme where you aren\u2019t locked to a certain set of abilities and perks based on a class, instead you\u2019ll create your own playstyle by picking the abilities and perks and cyberware you see fit.Be cool to see how branching will this thing be, how much can we just go off in one direction without having to supplement with other skills that might not be particularly part of our playstyle from a role-playing point of view.",
