            "answer_text": "Dam straight I am. The Witcher 3 (theyre previous title) is currently my favorite video game for many reasons and the same people are currently working on something else. They are obviously going in a very different direction with this game what with the first person perspective and science fiction setting but as long as they keep the best parts of the witcher, namely fantastic storytelling, detailed side quests and well written characters the setting and camera perspective shouldn't be a problem. I generally try to dampen my excitement for upcoming video games because i feel that its setting myself up for disappointment but I cant help it in this case. Every successive title CD Projekt Red has made has gotten progressively better. The Witcher 1 was mediocre, The Witcher 2 was really good and The Witcher 3 was fantastic and if the trend continues Cyberpunk will be unbelievable. ",
